CTU  FEE  Admissions  How to apply - Erasmus Plus Students



How to apply - Erasmus Plus Students
Thank you for your interest in studying at the Faculty of Electrical Engineering, CTU in Prague. Please note that you can study at our faculty under the Erasmus Plus programme only if your home university has an Erasmus agreement with CTU Prague. If not the student has the opportunity to study at the Faculty of Electrical Engineering on a fee-paying basis as a Degree student or through the One Semester Project.
How to apply

Step 1
Nomination
    If you wish to come to study at CTU in Prague as an Erasmus or an exchange student, your university must officially nominate you. Please contact your LLP - Erasmus coordinator or exchange coordinator.
Step 2
On-line registration
    On-line registration is available at the following website: https://mobility.cvut.cz/registration/
Step 3
Confirmation of Essential Forms:
Application Form + Learning Agreement + Language Certificate - please check the final deadlines here.
Step 4
Sending documents
    Copies signed by the home university must reach (mailed, faxed, e-mailed) the contact person for incoming students, Mrs. Lucie Bilova (lucie.bilova@cvut.cz)
The mailing address is: 
    MRS. LUCIE BILOVA
    INTERNATIONAL OFFICE OF CTU IN PRAGUE
    ZIKOVA 4, 166 36, PRAGUE 6
    CZECH REPUBLIC
Please check CTU web for complete informations
 The applications received after the application deadline are not accepted. 
Official Erasmus details:
  Czech Technical University in Prague, Faculty of Electrical Engineering
  Erasmus ID code: CZ PRAHA 10
  EUC (Erasmus charter) no: 51698-IC-1-2007-1CZ-ERASMUS-EUCX-1



